[b]Volume Strata[/b]

[b]What it does[/b]
Draws a fixed-range volume profile anchored to the right edge of your lookback window. Instead of floating to the left of the range, the profile grows leftward into the candle area — so the bars sit on top of the actual price action they represent. You see where volume clustered, which levels are dominant, and how buy and sell pressure distributed across the range.

[b]Key features[/b]
[list]
[*][b]Right-anchored bars[/b] — up-volume is shown on the inner (right) side of each row, down-volume extends further left. The split is determined per candle using body/wick weighting, not a simple close-above-open rule.
[*][b]Value area highlight[/b] — the configurable value area (default 70%) is shaded distinctly. Rows outside the area use lighter tones so the structure reads at a glance.
[*][b]Point of Control (POC)[/b] — dashed line at the highest-volume row, with a floating price label to the right. Color and width are configurable.
[*][b]VAH / VAL lines[/b] — dotted boundaries at the top and bottom of the value area, each with a price label. Toggle independently.
[*][b]HVN markers[/b] — small gold ticks appear to the right of the profile for any row where volume exceeds mean + 1σ. These are the highest-conviction reaction zones in the range.
[*][b]Info table[/b] — compact panel (top right) showing POC, VAH, VAL, and the buy-volume percentage. Buy% is colored green above 55%, red below 45%, and gray when balanced.
[/list]

[b]How to read it[/b]
[list]
[*]Wide rows = high acceptance — price spent time and attracted volume here; expect support/resistance on revisits.
[*]Thin rows (especially between HVNs) = low-volume nodes — price tends to move quickly through these.
[*]HVN markers (gold) = the strongest magnetic levels in the range.
[*]Up-volume wider than down on a row = more buying pressure at that level. Down-volume wider = more selling.
[*]Buy% in the table gives a quick read on overall directional bias across the full range.
[/list]

[b]Settings[/b]
[list]
[*][b]Lookback Bars[/b] — how many bars the range covers (1–500)
[*][b]Rows[/b] — number of price buckets (5–100); more rows = finer granularity
[*][b]Value Area %[/b] — percentage of total volume defining the value area (classic: 70%)
[*]All lines, colors, and toggles are grouped under Colors and Display in the inputs panel
[/list]

